One Adeyeni Adeyeye, 35, on Thursday was arraigned before an Osun State Magistrates’ Court, Ile-Ife for allegedly leading his son to beat up the school principal of Oduduwa College, Sanusi Ademola. He was arraigned on a six-count of conspiracy, stealing, assault, wilful damage and breach of public peace. Police prosecutor Abdullahi Emmanuel told the court that Adeyeye “invaded Oduduwa College, Ile-Ife with thugs and assaulted the principal by hitting him with fist blows, and tore his shirt. “He also assaulted one Awoyeye Olayide by hitting her with fist blows and stole her car key, office key and a purse containing cash sum of N50,000.”